commit.title: Allow make clean to work on a fresh clone
commit.message:
Allow make clean to work on a fresh clone

The file `config/Makefile` doesn't exist unless we run `./configure`.
We shouldn't have to run `./configure` to run `make clean`.  We still
error if we try to make any non-clean target in the test-suite Makefile
without first running configure; I did it this way because it is the
minimal change in behavior.  The simpler change would just be to never
error if `config/Makefile` doesn't exist (just change `include
../config/Makefile` to `-include ../config/Makefile`).

We also now test this property when building on CI.

This fixes #7542
